The paper deals with channel estimation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of sparsity-aware modifications of the LMS algorithm suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis of the algorithm's performance involves mathematical derivations and quantitative analysis, which may also place the paper under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistics (cs.SI).
